initial statement:
 932
Your Honor,

I stand before this court today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and understand the seriousness of the offense.

The offense occurred when I, without realizing the consequences, got behind the wheel and drove to a nearby supermarket. Admittedly, I failed to consider the court's previous order and the fact that I was disqualified from driving. I fully acknowledge my mistake, and I am truly embarrassed that I let this happen.

I am 55 years old and, other than the recent disqualification, I have maintained a clean criminal record. I have always strived to abide by the law and take responsibility for my actions. This incident is an anomaly in an otherwise law-abiding life.

I am fully committed to making amends for my mistake and preventing it from happening again. If given the opportunity, I am willing to undertake any necessary courses or programs that will further educate me on the consequences of my actions and aid in my rehabilitation. I understand that this is a serious matter and I am prepared to take the necessary steps to rectify my behavior.

Your Honor, I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding in light of my plea of guilty. I believe it is important to acknowledge that by accepting responsibility for my actions, I am already demonstrating remorse and a desire to change. I assure the court that I will use this experience as a pivotal opportunity for personal growth and to become a responsible member of society once again.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,
David Lambert
