I, David Lambert, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I would like to express my deep remorse for my actions and offer my sincerest apologies for failing to comply with the court's previous order.

I acknowledge that my decision to drive to the supermarket while knowing that I was disqualified from driving is inexcusable. I should have considered the consequences more seriously and respected the court's decision. I am truly sorry for my lack of judgment and understand the severity of my actions.

I want to emphasize that I have no criminal record, aside from the four speeding incidents that led to my disqualification. However, I take full responsibility for my current offense and do not intend to use those incidents as an excuse. My guilty plea is strictly related to driving whilst disqualified.

Throughout my life, it has always been my goal to be a law-abiding citizen and a responsible member of society. I deeply regret that my actions have let down both the court and my own personal values. I assure you that this incident is entirely out of character for me.

I am fully aware of the implications of my actions and the seriousness of disregarding the conditions of my disqualification. I am committed to making amends and taking active steps towards rectifying my behavior. If the court deems it necessary, I am prepared to willingly undertake any recommended courses or engage in activities that will facilitate my personal growth and help prevent any further misconduct.

Once again, I express my sincere apologies for my actions and any inconvenience or disappointment they may have caused. I am genuinely remorseful for my behavior and will do everything within my power to ensure that I never repeat such an offense in the future.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Yours faithfully,
David Lambert
